---
import "./Approach.css";
---
<section class="remodel-section">
    <div class="remodel-container">
        <h2>How Much Does a Kitchen Remodel Cost in Maryland?</h2>
        <p class="remodel-desc">
            See the average investment by kitchen size — and what’s included in each remodel.<br/>
            If you’re planning to remodel your kitchen in Maryland, it’s important to understand the typical investment based on kitchen size. Whether you’re upgrading a compact space or designing a luxury cooking area, this guide gives you a general price range for small, medium, and large kitchens — and what’s usually included in each.
        </p>
        <p class="remodel-note">
            *Prices shown are estimates and may vary depending on materials, finishes, structural changes, and overall project complexity.
        </p>
        <div class="remodel-grid">
            <div class="remodel-card">
                <img src="public/KitchenPage/kitchen5.png" alt="Small Kitchen Remodel" />
                <h3>Small Kitchen</h3>
                <div class="remodel-size">Under 70 ft²</div>
                <div class="remodel-price">$12,000 – $20,000*</div>
                <ul>
                    <li>Built-in compact appliances</li>
                    <li>Quartz countertops & LED lighting</li>
                    <li>Sleek storage solutions</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="remodel-card-desc">
                    Efficient, modern upgrades for tight spaces.<br/>
                    Smart layouts like one-wall or L-shape. Ideal for apartments and older homes.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="remodel-card">
                <img src="public/KitchenPage/kitchen6.png" alt="Medium Kitchen Remodel" />
                <h3>Medium Kitchen</h3>
                <div class="remodel-size">70 – 150 ft²</div>
                <div class="remodel-price">$20,000 – $40,000*</div>
                <ul>
                    <li>Custom cabinetry</li>
                    <li>Quartz or granite counters</li>
                    <li>Lighting upgrades</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="remodel-card-desc">
                    Balanced design for everyday comfort and function.<br/>
                    More flexible layouts like U-shape or galley. Found in townhomes and standard homes.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="remodel-card">
                <img src="public/KitchenPage/kitchen7.png" alt="Large Kitchen Remodel" />
                <h3>Large Kitchen</h3>
                <div class="remodel-size">Over 150 ft²</div>
                <div class="remodel-price">$40,000 – $70,000+*</div>
                <ul>
                    <li>Walk-in pantries & double ovens</li>
                    <li>Waterfall countertops</li>
                    <li>Designer lighting</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="remodel-card-desc">
                    Luxury spaces for family living and entertaining.<br/>
                    Spacious layouts with islands and premium finishes.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="remodel-cta">
            <button type="button">Request your free quote →</button>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>